Python code cheat sheet


1) for finding size of lists or set - len()
2) defining set or list in python
    a = list()
    b = set()
3) python list has append - a.append("1")
4) python set has add - b.add("1")
5) python operators
      1) % - gets reminder 
      2) // - gets integer quotient
6) bin() function in python returns the binary version of a specified integer
7) zfill() - returns a copy of the string with ‘0’ characters padded to the left side of the given string
8) 

# Ensure the number is within the 32-bit range
    number = number & 0xFFFFFFFF

    here we are doing bitwise and to restrict the length of bits to be within 32 bit range

9) ** - operator to find power of a number
10) >> - The left operand’s value is moved toward right by the number of bits 
11) << - The left operand’s value is moved toward left by the number of bits 
12) we can define map like map = {}
	to check values in key just check in map and for values - map.values()
	eg code:
	  if "apple" in map - This checks values in keys
	  if "apple" in map.values() - This checks values in values itself

13) For XOR operation - use this symbol - ^